               <msContents>
                  <summary>Request to inherit on papyrus from Oxyrhynchos (modern name: Bahnasa), Egypt. Aurelius Dionysius, a minor also known as Pausanias, assisted by his guardian, Artemidorus, son of Didymus both citizens of Oxyrhynchos, requests that the praefectus Aegypti or prefect of Egypt assign him the inheritance of his mother Aurelia whose real name ends  in "tarion," daughter of Sinthonis and citizen of Antinoopolis</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
